Around his neck, a serpent coils, representing the kundalini energy that lies dormant within every human being. In his right hand, he holds the trishul, a trident that symbolizes the three aspects of existence – creation, preservation, and destruction. With its sharp edges, the trident cuts through ignorance and leads to higher consciousness. In his left hand, Shiva holds a damaru, a small pellet drum that produces the primal sound of creation. The beat of the drum inspires divine energy and wisdom within those who hear it. As Lord Shiva stands atop Kailash, he represents the eternal cycle of life and death, the interconnectedness of all things, and the ultimate realization of the self.
